transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. Joanna speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi. How are you today?

Speaker 1: I'm doing well, sir. How are you?

Speaker 2: Not bad. I was wondering if you could help me cancel the subscription I got of the scorebook.

Speaker 1: Okay. I can assist you, sir. I have your account pulled up.

Speaker 2: I see you're a VIP status customer. Can you just confirm your date of birth for me?

Speaker 1: April 24, 1960.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you, Mr. Brown.

Speaker 1: And so what I'm noticing is that currently your account is set up to receive refills on a monthly basis,

Speaker 2: but we're not a subscription, so you're not locked into monthly fees or required to get your refills every month.

Speaker 1: The prescription written out by the doctor came available with refills,

Speaker 2: and as our customer, you can determine the frequency of your orders or put a pause on your account at any time.

Speaker 1: That way you can still retain your VIP pricing as well as have a prescription on hand with refills when you want to place a future order.

Speaker 2: Because if I cancel it entirely, it will cancel your prescription, and you won't be able to place refills again.

Speaker 1: That's actually what I need to do because I'm on a heart medication now where I can't use these type of drugs.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah. Well, thank you for letting us know that some of your medical conditions had changed,

Speaker 1: and your doctor advised that he does not recommend you to take this Viagra even though it's FDA approved?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay. Not a problem, sir. I'll go ahead and cancel any future orders.

Speaker 2: You do have the option to pause it, though. Did you want to pause it until July?

Speaker 1: No, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay. You can always call in and extend that hold, too, if needed.

Speaker 1: Do you want to cancel it entirely?

Speaker 2: Yes, please.

Speaker 1: Okay. You got it, sir. You've been canceled, Mr. Brown.

Speaker 2: All right. Will they send a confirmation?

Speaker 1: I'm not sure if you'll get a confirmation email, but if you log into your account online,

Speaker 2: you'll see that all future orders have been canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, thank you for your help.

Speaker 2: My pleasure. Thanks for calling in. Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye now.

Speaker 2: Bye.
